## UI Implementation

### Progress Indicator Location

The progress message appears in the existing **progress bar** element:

```html
<div id="progress" style="display: none;">
  <div class="spinner"></div>
  <div id="progressText">Processing...</div>
</div>
```

### CSS Styling

The progress bar already has styling:
- Blue spinner animation
- Bold text for the message
- Centered alignment
- Visible during processing, hidden when complete

---

## Code Flow

### 1. User Uploads File

```javascript
// popup.js - detectPII()
showProgress(true, 'Detecting PII...');
```

### 2. NER Detection Starts

```javascript
// popup.js - detectWithNER()
const results = await window.nerPipeline.predict(text, (message) => {
  showProgress(true, message);
});
```

### 3. Custom NER Loader Updates Progress

```javascript
// custom-ner-loader.js - predictWithSlidingWindow()
if (progressCallback) {
  progressCallback(`Processing chunk ${i + 1}/${chunks.length} (${percentage}%)...`);
}
```

### 4. UI Updates in Real-Time

```javascript
// popup.js - showProgress()
document.getElementById('progressText').textContent = message;
```

### 5. Detection Completes

```javascript
// popup.js - detectPII()
showProgress(false);
showStatus(`Detected ${detections.length} PII item(s)`, 'success');
```

---

## Benefits

### User Experience

✅ **Transparency**: Users see exactly what's happening
✅ **Confidence**: Progress bar shows the process isn't stuck
✅ **Expectations**: Percentage helps estimate time remaining
✅ **Feedback**: Real-time updates every chunk (every ~0.5s)

### Developer Experience

✅ **Simple API**: Just pass a callback function
✅ **No breaking changes**: progressCallback is optional
✅ **Backward compatible**: Works with old code (no callback)
✅ **Flexible**: Can update any UI element via callback

---

## Comparison: Before vs After

### Before (No Progress UI)

```
User uploads file
  ↓
"Detecting PII..." (appears)
  ↓
[30 seconds of silence]
  ↓
"Detected 142 PII item(s)" (appears)
```

**User thinks:** "Is it frozen? Should I wait? Is it working?"

---

### After (With Progress UI)

```
User uploads file
  ↓
"Processing large document: 57 chunks (22553 tokens)"
  ↓
"Processing chunk 1/57 (2%)..."
"Processing chunk 2/57 (4%)..."
"Processing chunk 3/57 (5%)..."
...
"Processing chunk 57/57 (100%)..."
  ↓
"Merging results (found 167 entities)..."
  ↓
"Completed: 142 unique entities detected"
  ↓
"Detected 142 PII item(s)"
```

**User sees:** Clear progress, knows it's working, can estimate time remaining

---

## Edge Cases

### Case 1: Very Fast Processing

If chunks process very quickly (<100ms each), updates might flash by:

**Solution:** Progress bar is designed for this - it's okay if updates are fast

---

### Case 2: Network/CPU Slowdown

If processing slows down, progress updates show this:

```
Processing chunk 20/57 (35%)...  [2 seconds]
Processing chunk 21/57 (37%)...  [5 seconds - slow!]
```

**User benefit:** Knows the system is still working, just slower

---

### Case 3: Single Chunk Documents

For documents ≤512 tokens:

```
Processing document...  [<1 second]
Detected X PII item(s)
```

**User benefit:** Simple, fast, no chunking info needed

---

## Future Enhancements

### 1. Progress Bar (Visual)

Add a visual progress bar:

```html
<div class="progress-bar">
  <div class="progress-fill" style="width: 35%"></div>
</div>
<div>Processing chunk 20/57 (35%)...</div>
```

### 2. Time Remaining Estimate

Calculate estimated time remaining:

```
Processing chunk 20/57 (35%)...
Estimated time remaining: 18 seconds
```

### 3. Cancel Button

Allow users to cancel long-running operations:

```html
<button id="cancelProcessing">Cancel</button>
```

```javascript
if (userCancelled) {
  throw new Error('Processing cancelled by user');
}
```

### 4. Detailed Stats

Show more information:

```
Processing chunk 20/57 (35%)
Found 45 entities so far
Speed: 2.5 chunks/second
```

